.TH SUTURE-AUDIT "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-audit \- Inspect the tamper\-evident audit log
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture audit [\\fIoptions\\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Inspect the tamper\-evident audit log.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-verify
Verify chain integrity
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-show
Display all entries
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-count
Show entry count
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-tail \\fI<n>\\fR
Show last N entries (default: 10)
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
